The paper introduces a new layer for feed-forward neural networks and focuses on improving their interpretability and compressibility. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of data features in training, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper employs tensor decompositions, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
